window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Edited by National Book Award finalist Ibi Zoboi and featuring some of the most acclaimed best-selling black authors writing for teens today - </b><b><i>Black Enough</i></b><b> is an essential collection of captivating stories about what it’s like to be young and black in America.</b></p> <p><b>A selection of the Schomburg Center's Black Liberation Reading List.</b></p> <p>Black is...sisters navigating their relationship at summer camp in Portland, Oregon, as written by Renée Watson.</p> <p>Black is...three friends walking back from the community pool talking about nothing and everything, in a story by Jason Reynolds.</p> <p>Black is...Nic Stone’s high-class beauty dating a boy of whom her momma would never approve.</p> <p>Black is...two girls kissing in Justina Ireland’s story set in Maryland.</p> <p>Black is urban and rural, wealthy and poor, mixed race, immigrants, and more - because there are countless ways to be Black enough.</p> <p><b>Contributors:</b></p> <p></p> <ul> <li>Justina Ireland</li> <li>Varian Johnson</li> <li>Rita Williams-Garcia</li> <li>Dhonielle Clayton</li> <li>Kekla Magoon</li> <li>Leah Henderson</li> <li>Tochi Onyebuchi</li> <li>Jason Reynolds</li> <li>Nic Stone</li> <li>Liara Tamani</li> <li>Renée Watson</li> <li>Tracey Baptiste</li> <li>Coe Booth</li> <li>Brandy Colbert</li> <li>Jay Coles</li> <li>Ibi Zoboi</li> <li>Lamar Giles</li> </ul>"; 
